{"event": "model_answer", "response": "Here is a list of all the tools available to me, organized by their primary functions:\n\n### \ud83d\ude80 Audit Execution & Status\n*   **`start_audit_run`**: Start a server-side audit run on specified devices with specific commands.\n*   **`list_audit_runs`**: List all active or recent audit runs currently stored in server memory.\n*   **`get_audit_run_status`**: Get the current status metadata (e.g., pending, running, completed) for a specific run.\n*   **`get_audit_run_summary`**: Get a compact, high-level summary of an audit run.\n*   **`list_run_commands`**: List the commands that were captured during a specific run.\n\n### \ud83d\udd0d Results & Context Analysis\n*   **`get_analysis_context`**: Get the best available context for an analysis (returns structured data if available, otherwise raw output).\n*   **`get_audit_host_details`**: Retrieve all command results for a single specific host from a run.\n*   **`get_audit_command_details`**: Retrieve the result of a specific command on a specific host.\n*   **`get_raw_command_outputs`**: Fetch the raw output for a specific command across multiple hosts.\n*   **`get_raw_analysis_context`**: Retrieve the most relevant raw evidence to answer a specific question (useful when no structured parser exists).\n*   **`search_raw_command_outputs`**: Search raw command outputs for specific keywords/queries and return matching excerpts.\n*   **`search_audit_results`**: Search text across an entire run and return matching host/command pairs.\n\n### \ud83e\udde9 Hardware & Component Analysis\n*   **`count_components`**: Count specific hardware components (like line cards, routing engines) across devices.\n*   **`list_components`**: List structured details of components found on the devices.\n*   **`summarize_components`**: Provide a summary of all structured components grouped by type and description.\n*   **`get_host_component_summary`**: Get structured component summaries grouped by each host.\n\n### \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f Device Actions & Configuration\n*   **`ping_from_device`**: Execute a ping from one specific device (source) to another (target) and parse latency stats.\n*   **`ping_device`**: A legacy compatibility wrapper for pinging a device (I will usually ask you for a source and target to use `ping_from_device` instead).\n*   **`collect_bng_configuration`**: Collect BNG configurations using `admin display-config`, save the original, and convert it to a flat format.\n*   **`flatten_sros_config`**: Convert pasted, hierarchical SR OS configuration text into a flat format.\n\n### \ud83d\udcdc Historical Logs & Persistence\n*   **`list_audit_log_runs`**: List all older, persisted audit run logs saved on the disk.\n*   **`get_audit_log_summary`**: Get the summary for a historical, persisted audit run.\n*   **`get_audit_log_host_details`**: Retrieve detailed host results from a historical, persisted log.\n*   **`get_audit_run_log_path`**: Return the exact log file path on the server for a specific run.\n\nFeel free to ask if you'd like me to start an audit, check previous logs, perform a ping, or parse a configuration!", "route": "adk", "session_id": "0e6ff8885085", "timestamp": 1778002005.7083278, "turn_id": "9a88404ecd7a"}
