{"event": "model_answer", "response": "Here are all the tools currently available to me:\n\n### \ud83d\ude80 Audit Execution & Diagnostics\n*   **`start_audit_run`**: Start a server-side audit run to execute commands on specified devices.\n*   **`ping_from_device`**: Execute a ping from a specific source device to a target device and return latency stats.\n*   **`ping_device`**: Compatibility wrapper for pinging a device (requires a source device).\n\n### \u2699\ufe0f Configuration Utilities\n*   **`collect_bng_configuration`**: Collect BNG configuration using `admin display-config`, save the original, and convert it into a flat format.\n*   **`flatten_sros_config`**: Convert hierarchical SR OS configuration text into a flat format.\n\n### \ud83d\udcca Audit Status & Summaries\n*   **`list_audit_runs`**: List all audit runs currently stored in server memory.\n*   **`get_audit_run_status`**: Return status metadata (e.g., pending, running) for a specific run.\n*   **`get_audit_run_summary`**: Return a compact summary for a run.\n*   **`list_run_commands`**: List the commands captured for a specific run.\n\n### \ud83d\udd0d Detailed Results & Analysis Context\n*   **`get_analysis_context`**: Return the best available analysis context (structured data if a parser exists, otherwise raw output).\n*   **`get_audit_host_details`**: Return all command results for a single host.\n*   **`get_audit_command_details`**: Return a single host/command result.\n*   **`get_raw_command_outputs`**: Return raw outputs for a command across matching hosts.\n*   **`search_raw_command_outputs`**: Search raw outputs for a command and return matching excerpts.\n*   **`get_raw_analysis_context`**: Return the most relevant raw evidence for a question (for commands without parsers).\n*   **`search_audit_results`**: Search result text across the run and return matching host/command pairs.\n\n### \ud83e\udde9 Hardware & Components\n*   **`count_components`**: Count specific hardware components (e.g., exact, prefix, or contains match).\n*   **`list_components`**: List structured components found on the devices.\n*   **`summarize_components`**: Summarize all structured components by type and exact description.\n*   **`get_host_component_summary`**: Return structured component summaries grouped by host.\n\n### \ud83d\udcc1 Historical Audit Logs\n*   **`list_audit_log_runs`**: List persisted audit run logs saved on disk.\n*   **`get_audit_log_summary`**: Return the persisted summary for a prior run.\n*   **`get_audit_log_host_details`**: Return host details from a persisted log.\n*   **`get_audit_run_log_path`**: Return the log file path for a specific run.\n\nLet me know if you would like to use any of these! For example, we could explore the components on your recent run (`f12e37a293d5`) using `summarize_components` or `count_components`.", "route": "adk", "session_id": "0e6ff8885085", "timestamp": 1778006120.8951519, "turn_id": "db830952d287"}
